node.text: NATO’s AGS "Phoenix" Global Hawk fleet continues to rack up flight hours as the high-altitude, long-endurance aircraft that it is.

node.text: Northrop Grumman’s flexible work schedule gives me the opportunity to continue my studies, allowing me to apply the theory I learn into the practical work on-site. #NationalInternDay

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Northrop Grumman on July 29, 2021. May be an image of 2 people, people sitting, eyeglasses and indoor.

node.text: Here in the control room, testing is observed safely while being recorded in real-time. #NationalInternDay

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Northrop Grumman on July 29, 2021. May be an image of 1 person, standing and indoor.

node.text: We also get to test larger motors. As safety is one of the top priorities at Northrop Grumman, only required personnel can be in the control room area during testing. #NationalInternDay

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Northrop Grumman on July 29, 2021. May be an image of one or more people and outdoors.

node.text: Despite the size, this motor packs a punch! Here's the test bay where the motor is mounted and fired. This allows us to see if it’s meeting the performance requirements. #NationalInternDay

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Northrop Grumman on July 29, 2021. May be an image of 1 person, outdoors and text that says 'NO TOOLING OR FLIGHT HARDWARE ALLOWED THRIS THIS G-15 METAL PARTS INSPECTION'.

node.text: At this area, the motors and components are inspected to make sure they meet all drawing requirements, which helps us make sure they're fit for use. #NationalInternDay

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Northrop Grumman on July 29, 2021. May be an image of 1 person and indoor.

node.text: As a part of the process, I get to work with motors and see if they're performing to the required standards. #NationalInternDay

node.text: Hey y’all! My name is Cristina and I'm an #engineering intern. I get to experience extensive hands-on work, so I'll be showing you some of the work I do here at Northrop Grumman!  #NationalInternDay
